# ClickUp Automation

## Hierarchy
```
Workspace (Team) > Space > Folder > List > Task
```

**Note**: Lists can be inside Folders OR directly in Spaces (folderless).

## ID Formats
| Entity | Format |
|--------|--------|
| Workspace/Team | Large integers |
| Space, Folder, List | Integers |
| Task | Alphanumeric strings (e.g., "9hz") |
| User | Integers |
| Comment | Integers |

## Task Creation
| Parameter | Notes |
|-----------|-------|
| `list_id` | Integer, required |
| `name` | String, required |
| `status` | **Case-sensitive**, must match list status |
| `priority` | 1=Urgent, 2=High, 3=Normal, 4=Low |
| `due_date` | Unix timestamp in **milliseconds** |
| `assignees` | Array of user IDs (integers) |

## Subtasks
- `parent`: Parent task ID (string)
- Parent must be a task (not another subtask)
- Parent must be in the same list

## Comments
All four fields required:
- `task_id`
- `comment_text`
- `assignee` (assigns comment, not task)
- `notify_all`

## Pagination
- Tasks: `page` starts at 0, max 100 per page
- Comments: `start` (Unix ms) + `start_id`, max 25 per page

## Gotchas
- `team_id` = Workspace ID (not a user group)
- Dates are milliseconds (multiply seconds Ã— 1000)
- Status must match exactly (case-sensitive)
- Use `CLICKUP_GET_LIST` to see available statuses

## Best Practices
- Resolve names to IDs through hierarchy
- Check available statuses before creating tasks
- Set `notify_all=false` for bulk operations
- Track created task IDs to avoid duplicate retries
